<p><b>Melvyn Bragg, Baron Bragg</b>, <a href="Royal_Society" title="Royal Society">FRS</a>, <a href="British_Academy" title="British Academy">FBA</a>, <a href="Royal_Society_of_Arts" title="Royal Society of Arts">FRSA</a>, <a href="Royal_Society_of_Literature" title="Royal Society of Literature">FRSL</a>, <a href="Royal_Television_Society" title="Royal Television Society">FRTS</a> (born 6 October 1939), is an English broadcaster and author, best known for his work with the <a href="BBC" title="BBC">BBC</a> and for <a href="ITV" title="ITV" class="mw-redirect">ITV</a> presenting the <i><a href="The_South_Bank_Show" title="The South Bank Show">The South Bank Show</a></i> (1978–2010). Since 1998 he has presented over 550 weekly episodes of the BBC Radio discussion programme <i><a href="In_Our_Time_(BBC_Radio_4)" title="In Our Time (BBC Radio 4)">In Our Time</a></i>.</p>
