<li id="cite_note-11"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-11">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation news">Guinness, Daphne (14 July 2008). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.smh.com.au/news/books/melvyn-in-the-middle/2008/06/13/1213321586009.html?page=fullpage#contentSwap1">"Melvyn in the Middle"</a>. <i>Sydney Morning Herald</i><span class="printonly">. <a rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="http://www.smh.com.au/news/books/melvyn-in-the-middle/2008/06/13/1213321586009.html?page=fullpage#contentSwap1">http://www.smh.com.au/news/books/melvyn-in-the-middle/2008/06/13/1213321586009.html?page=fullpage#contentSwap1</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved 14 July 2008</span>. "...my first wife was an aristocrat. I didn't know that for a year."</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-12"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-12">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.guardian.co.uk/Columnists/Column/0,,1500897,00.html">"Plato or Nietzsche? You choose", <i>The Guardian</i>.</a></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-smh.com.au-13"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-smh.com.au_13-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation web"><a href="Daphne_Guinness" title="Daphne Guinness">Daphne Guinness</a> (14 June 2008). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.smh.com.au/news/books/melvyn-in-the-middle/2008/06/13/1213321586009.html?page=fullpage">"Melvyn in the middle"</a>. <i>Sydney Morning Herald</i><span class="printonly">. <a rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="http://www.smh.com.au/news/books/melvyn-in-the-middle/2008/06/13/1213321586009.html?page=fullpage">http://www.smh.com.au/news/books/melvyn-in-the-middle/2008/06/13/1213321586009.html?page=fullpage</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved 2011-10-04</span>.</span></span></li>
